% Chapter 4: Examples of Extending the System
% File: ./intrfc.xml (line 13)
% Who: Thomas Breuer
% Started: January 24, 2008
% Finished: August 10, 2008
% Comments:
- In ``Extending the Range of Definition ...'', explain redeclaring
  operations? (For packages, this is anyhow necessary.)
- In ``Enforcing Property Tests'', one finds ``As mentioned above''.
  This is not very useful if one does not assume that someone reads the
  whole book.  So we should try to avoid such formulations, and to give
  explicit references instead.
  (This is of course a general statement for the whole documentation.)
- Section ``Adding a new Operation'' starts with ``The next step''
  --what does this refer to?
- Section ``Components versus Attributes'' is not appropriate.
  For example, the aspect that the knowledge of attribute values can be
  used in the method selection is not mentioned.
  (And why do attributes need *two* filter bits?)
- It should be stated which of the examples shown in the chapter are
  ``ficticious'' (not part of the GAP library) and which are taken from
  the library.
  For example, there is an example which introduces a new property
  `IsMGroup', whereas the GAP library uses the similar filter
  `IsMonomial'.
- The description of categories vs. properties in ``Adding new Concepts''
  is not correct.
- Again there are cross-references to undocumented functions
  (NormalizerOp, GroupByGenerators).
- overfull box because of a long list label in the ManSection for
  `ArithmeticElementCreator' --how to deal with this?
- Finally, the two sections ``Adding new Concepts'' and
  ``Creating Own Arithmetic Objects'' both start with ``finally''.
